comment_data.body: As far as I can tell, this is unused

Wouldn't it much nicer to use Tempita for this?

In the utility code you write
```
__PYX_HAVE_RT_ImportType_proto_{{HASH}}
```

and then you just load it with
```
TempitaUtilityCode.load_cached("TypeImport", "ImportExport.c", context={'HASH': cy_version})
```
Disregard my comment. Your approach works just fine, it is easier, and it is used everywhere.
There used to be a `__Pyx_ImportModule()` that employed it. Probably still needed in 0.29.x.

Looks like `__Pyx_PyIdentifier_FromString` is also unused in branch 0.29.x. 

```
$ git grep PyIdentifier
Cython/Compiler/ModuleNode.py:            h_code.put(UtilityCode.load_as_string("PyIdentifierFromString", "ImportExport.c")[0])
Cython/Utility/ImportExport.c://///////////// PyIdentifierFromString.proto ///////////////
Cython/Utility/ImportExport.c:#if !defined(__Pyx_PyIdentifier_FromString)
Cython/Utility/ImportExport.c:  #define __Pyx_PyIdentifier_FromString(s) PyString_FromString(s)
Cython/Utility/ImportExport.c:  #define __Pyx_PyIdentifier_FromString(s) PyUnicode_FromString(s)
```

commit.message:
Distinguish api import functions from cython versions

Fixes issue with changed signature for these functions between
Cython releases
Tidy up the output with lines

milestone.description:
Goals:
 New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
 Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3str`.
 Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
 Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
